- **Discovery of a molecular glue promoting CDK12-DDB1 interaction to trigger cyclin K degradation (PubMed)**  
  URL: `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/32804079/`  
  Quote snippets:  
  - “a new molecular glue **HQ461**”  
  - “A provisional patent application (**PCT/CN2020/095482**) has been filed” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/32804079/))

- **WO2023203174A1 — Heterocyclic cullin ring ubiquitin ligase compounds and uses thereof (Google Patents) — Proxygen**  
  URL: `https://patents.google.com/patent/WO2023203174A1/en`  
  Quote snippets:  
  - “Publication number **WO2023203174A1**”  
  - “Current Assignee … **Proxygen GmbH**”  
  - “the **CDK12/Cyclin K** interacts with a CRL complex comprises **CUL4A** or **CUL4B** and **DDB1**.” ([patents.google.com](https://patents.google.com/patent/WO2023203174A1/en))

- **WO2021176049A1 — Pyrazolopyrazines agissant sur des cancers par inhibition de cdk12 (Google Patents)**  
  URL: `https://patents.google.com/patent/WO2021176049A1/fr`  
  Quote snippets:  
  - “Publication number **WO2021176049A1**”  
  - “compounds which induce the proteolytic degradation of **CDK12** and/or **Cyclin K** in the cell.”  
  - “for the treatment of lung cancer, breast cancer, liver cancer, colorectal cancer, gastric cancer, prostate cancer and leukemia.” ([patents.google.com](https://patents.google.com/patent/WO2021176049A1/fr))
